cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories, as it deals with real-time segmentation of surgical instruments in robot-assisted surgery. The use of deep learning models also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed network on datasets suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
